<title>BELGIUM: Gevaert, Cobepa group shares to remain suspended.</title>
<headline>Gevaert, Cobepa group shares to remain suspended.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Brussels Stock Exchange said on Friday its decision to suspend trading in six companies which earlier announced a major realignment of their interests would remain in force until the end of the day.</p>
<p>&quot;The (bourse) committee has decided, given that the information has not yet been entirely diffused in the market, that the...shares will remain suspended until the end of this day,&quot; the bourse said in a statement.</p>
<p>The decision affects trade in holding companies Gevaert, Cobepa, Ibel, Almanij, Imperial Invest and Belvuco.</p>
<p>Gevaert earlier announced plans to split, with its assets being divided between the Almanij and Cobepa groups. The other companies mentioned are all affected by the deal.</p>
